<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="233" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,820,1554]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,820,845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Hermaphroditic. Rostrum obsolete. Linea thalassinica complete or nearly so. Thoracic sternite 
<number box="[1363,1377,821,844]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="7.0">7</number>
with narrow anterior part, slightly separating cushion-like coxae of pereopods 
<number box="[1007,1024,856,880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="4.0">4</number>
. Pleomere 
<number box="[1156,1170,856,880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
tergite with flat broad anterior part almost as wide as posterior part. Eyestalks flattened, contiguous, each with acute apex; pigmented cornea dorsal. Antennal scaphocerite minute and articulating. Maxilliped 
<number box="[1006,1020,927,951]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
merus without distal tooth, exopod reduced, with toothed crista dentata, ischium and merus without brush of stiff setae. Pereopods 
<number box="[1216,1230,962,986]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
similar or slightly dissimilar. Pereopod 
<number box="[387,401,998,1022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
propodus about 
<number box="[590,625,997,1022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as broad, with distal spiniform seta. Pereopod 
<number box="[1311,1325,998,1022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="4.0">4</number>
propodus without distal spiniform seta. Pereopod 
<number box="[597,611,1033,1058]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="5.0">5</number>
simple, dactylus closing on distal spiniform seta on propodus. Setal-rows on anterolateral carapace, pleomere 
<number box="[571,585,1069,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
and pleomere 
<number box="[761,775,1068,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="6.0">6</number>
(
<number box="[795,810,1069,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
rows). Pleopod 
<number box="[1004,1018,1069,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[1029,1043,1068,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
-articled. Pleopod 
<number box="[1256,1270,1069,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
with elongate appendix masculina with long terminal setae, appendix interna a fused thumb-like extension. Pleopods 
<number box="[1334,1376,1103,1128]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
rami without marginal filaments. Uropodal endopod without transverse row of short spiniform setae; exopod ovate, without dorsal plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,820,1554]" box="[199,1269,1210,1235]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">
